  "prompt": "How can I prepare for Tessolve technical round?",
  "response": "To prepare for the Tessolve technical round, here are some key steps and areas to focus on:\n\n1. Technical Knowledge Preparation:\n- Review core subjects like Digital Electronics\n- Brush up on Microcontrollers and Microprocessors\n- Study Computer Architecture\n- Understand Embedded Systems fundamentals\n- Learn about VLSI and Hardware Design\n\n2. Programming Skills:\n- Practice C and C++ programming\n- Strengthen your understanding of data structures and algorithms\n- Learn embedded C programming\n- Practice coding problems on platforms like HackerRank, LeetCode\n\n3. Key Technical Topics:\n- Digital Logic Design\n- Memory Interfacing\n- Processor Architecture\n- Communication Protocols (I2C, SPI, UART)\n- Assembly Language Programming\n- Interrupt Handling\n- Embedded System Design\n\n4. Hardware Knowledge:\n- Understand basic electronic components\n- Learn about different microcontroller families\n- Familiar with Arduino/Raspberry Pi platforms\n- Basic knowledge of PCB design\n\n5. Interview Preparation:\n- Practice problem-solving questions\n- Prepare technical project explanations\n- Review your resume thoroughly\n- Be ready to discuss your academic and project experiences\n\n6. Soft Skills:\n- Develop clear communication\n- Show problem-solving approach\n- Demonstrate enthusiasm for technology\n\n7. Additional Resources:\n- Reference books on embedded systems\n- Online tutorials\n- Technical forums and discussions",
